description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within our Intensive Care department for a Band 6 Senior Staff Nurse to join our team. We are seeking to appoint an experienced and motivated Critical Care Nurse, who has vision and enthusiasm for change and development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Homerton ICU we recognise that our team members are our greatest asset – it’s their hard work and effort that really makes a difference. That’s why we encourage our staff to fulfil their full potential. We’ll do everything we can to support you, along with offering excellent learning and development opportunities including a structured Band 6 Development Programme, shift management, Simulation training and the opportunity to lead on Practice Development projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have proven clinical skills and a post registration qualification in Critical Care, whilst showing enthusiasm and professionalism in the development of your leadership and management skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a warm welcome and a friendly working environment for your commitment to working internal rotation throughout the 24hr period, encompassing Bank Holidays and weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Homerton has a proud tradition of supporting and developing its staff, including its well-regarded and valued nursing community, and all staff are able to take advantage of a great range of benefits including salary sacrifice and discount schemes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This appointment will be subject to a satisfactory completion of a 6 month probationary period for new starters to the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lucy Jenkins Ph: 0208 510 7303 / Email: lucy.jenkins3@nhs.net&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
